The paper deals with the problem of ranking, which is a common task in machine learning and information retrieval. The paper proposes an efficient reduction of the ranking problem to binary classification, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the time complexity of the algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as well. Finally, the paper mentions applications in search engines, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
